    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1875-09-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1875-09-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="89"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d89">
                <head>No. 393.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bingham</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">United States Legation, Japan</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tokei</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1875-09-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 8, 1875</date>. (Received October
                        7.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 264.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report the arrival in this
                    capital of Brevet Major-General Upton, Brevet Brigadier-General Forsyth, and
                    Brevet Major Sanger, United States Army, under commission to examine and report
                    upon the military service in Japan and other countries in the East and in
                    Europe.</p>
                <p>General Upton handed me your circular of the 24th of June last, commending him to
                    the diplomatic and consular officers of the United States.</p>
                <p>In accordance with your instructions, I have extended to these gentlemen due
                    courtesy, and have presented them to the Japanese minister of war.</p>
                <p>To-day they were honored by a general review of the troops of the empire in the
                    capital.</p>
                <p>It gives me pleasure to say that these gentlemen have been most cordially
                    received by this government.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JNO. A. BINGHAM.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
